Here are some prompt ideas that would fit very naturally for a QM (Quality Management) Space Agent used by testers, QA engineers, auditors, and quality specialists.

You can mix:

Quick action prompts (short, clickable)

Guided prompts (more descriptive)

Scenario-based prompts (real tester workflow)



---

Recommended Replacement / Additional Prompts

Documentation & Standards

Find the relevant QM standard for...

Explain this testing requirement

Show the procedure for defect handling

What does the process say about...

Compare two QM procedures

Where is this covered in the documentation?

Summarize the key points of this standard

What changed in the latest process update?



---

Tester Support

What test evidence is required?

Help me prepare for a QA audit

What should I validate before release?

Explain the acceptance criteria for...

What are the mandatory QA checks?

Give me the testing workflow for this process

What risks should I consider here?

Help me understand this defect classification



---

Process Guidance

Which process applies in this situation?

What is the escalation path for this issue?

Show the approval workflow

What are the responsibilities of testers in this process?

When should a deviation be raised?

Explain the root cause analysis process

What is the correct CAPA procedure?

Which template should I use?



